@scaling01 You do realize that I've been advocating for end-to-end self-supervised training of world models and planning for about 10 years, made a lot of progress over the last 5, actually made it work for simple robotics tasks over the last 2, and just started a company to make it practical.
Not sure who's going to look like an idiot....
https://t.co/ObRKBnNWo8

@scaling01 A few robotics AI companies are working on world models, planning, etc.
But the vast majority are using LLM-derived methods, like VLA, or diffusion policies with RL fine-tuning in simulation. Nice for narrow tasks.
The companies building humanoid hardware don't tend to be the ones working on innovative robotics AI.

@nikitabier i'd argue or add that build-in-public is great if you're trying to figure out what you want to work on

in the case of clawbot/moltbot, the founder has tons of projects, but thanks to building-in-public, knows what is most interesting to people

(i had a similar exp w babyagi, and did not think it was special until i posted it on Twitter)

